You‚Äôre basically trying to embed a **Google Map with a pinned business card** inside React like the screenshot.

There are 3 ways to do it. Only one of them is ‚Äúproper‚Äù depending on what you need.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Quick & Dirty (Iframe embed) ‚Äî easiest

If all you need is a static map with the pin + info popup, don‚Äôt overengineer it.

### Steps

1. Go to Google Maps
2. Search your business
3. Click **Share ‚Üí Embed a map ‚Üí Copy HTML**
4. Use it inside React

### React Component

```jsx
import React from "react";

const MapEmbed = () => {
  return (
    <div style={{ width: "100%", height: "450px" }}>
      <iframe
        title="Gharuda Infotech Location"
        src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Gharuda+Infotech+Pvt+Ltd,+Chennai&output=embed"
        width="100%"
        height="100%"
        style={{ border: 0 }}
        allowFullScreen=""
        loading="lazy"
        referrerPolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
  );
};

export default MapEmbed;
```

‚úî Shows pin
‚úî Shows business card on click
‚ùå No customization
‚ùå No programmatic control

Use this if you just need display.

---

# 2Ô∏è‚É£ Proper React Integration (Google Maps JS API)

If you want:

* Custom marker
* Custom popup
* Dynamic locations
* Styling

Then you use the API.

---

## Install library

```bash
npm install @react-google-maps/api
```

---

## Basic Map with Marker + InfoWindow

```jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import {
  GoogleMap,
  LoadScript,
  Marker,
  InfoWindow,
} from "@react-google-maps/api";

const containerStyle = {
  width: "100%",
  height: "450px",
};

const center = {
  lat: 13.0615,   // Chennai approx
  lng: 80.2420,
};

const MapComponent = () => {
  const [showInfo, setShowInfo] = useState(false);

  return (
    <LoadScript googleMapsApiKey="YOUR_API_KEY">
      <GoogleMap mapContainerStyle={containerStyle} center={center} zoom={15}>
        
        <Marker
          position={center}
          onClick={() => setShowInfo(true)}
        />

        {showInfo && (
          <InfoWindow
            position={center}
            onCloseClick={() => setShowInfo(false)}
          >
            <div>
              <h3>Gharuda Infotech Pvt Ltd</h3>
              <p>
                2nd Floor, 129, Valluvarkottam High Rd,  
                Nungambakkam, Chennai
              </p>
              <p>‚≠ê 3.3 (9 reviews)</p>
            </div>
          </InfoWindow>
        )}

      </GoogleMap>
    </LoadScript>
  );
};

export default MapComponent;
```

---

## Get API Key

1. Go to Google Cloud Console
2. Enable **Maps JavaScript API**
3. Create credentials ‚Üí API key
4. Restrict it to your domain

Without this, map won‚Äôt load.

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ Business Card Like Screenshot (Places API)

The popup in your screenshot is not manual text.

That card comes from **Google Places data**.

If you want auto-fetched:

* Reviews
* Rating
* Address
* Photos

You must use:

üëâ Places API + Place ID

---

### Example flow

1. Get Place ID from Maps
2. Fetch details

```js
const service = new google.maps.places.PlacesService(map);

service.getDetails(
  { placeId: "YOUR_PLACE_ID" },
  (place, status) => {
    console.log(place);
  }
);
```

Then render inside InfoWindow.

This is the only way to replicate the real Google card dynamically.

---

# When to use what

| Use case                | Method      |
| ----------------------- | ----------- |
| Just show location      | Iframe      |
| Custom marker + popup   | Maps JS API |
| Real business data card | Places API  |

---

# Common mistakes (React devs keep screwing this up)

* Forgetting to enable billing ‚Üí map blocked
* Using API key in frontend without restriction
* Re-rendering map every state change
* Wrong lat/lng order
* Not setting container height ‚Üí map invisible

If your map is blank, it‚Äôs almost always one of these.

